headline: KeyCorp’s (NYSE:KEY) Q2 Sales Beat Estimates
summary: Regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 21.5% year on year to $1.84 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.35 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: KEYCORP REPORTS SECOND QUARTER 2025 NET INCOME OF $387 MILLION, OR $.35 PER DILUTED COMMON SHARE
summary: KeyCorp (NYSE: KEY) today announced net income from continuing operations attributable to Key common shareholders of $387 million, or $.35 per diluted common share, for the second quarter of 2025. For the first quarter of 2025, net income from continuing operations attributable to Key common shareholders was $370 million, or $.33 per diluted common share. For the second quarter of 2024, KeyCorp reported net income from continuing operations attributable to Key common shareholders of $237 million
